'''Postcount''' is the number of posts (replies and new threads) made by a user in an [[internet forum]]. Posts made in off topic forums are often not counted in postcounts.

==Impacts of post counts==

In some online communities, the title appearing beneath a user's display name changes by the number of posts a user has made. If a user has, for example, 499 posts, often, making another post, 500, will cause the title to change and it may not change again until it reaches 1000 posts. This is often a cause of [[Spam (electronic)#Forum spam|forum spam]]. Spammers make spam posts just to increase the post count and get a new title. These can range from obvious, to subtle, anecdotal posts.

Some have said "Remember kids, the higher your postcount, the bigger your penis is" but this is very arguable and most probably not true. Some facts to back this up are that most men (that have a penis) do not even visit forums, some do not even no what an internet forum is. There is no scientific proof on either side so the question remains: does having more postcount mean you can boast a larger penis? We may never know.

